messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 2/3/2000 5:20:48 PM Central Standard Time,
liv2learn@... writes:

<< It's called "Discount School Supply." I first got their catalog from a
friend, then saw the site online. >>
We order from Discount School Supply too. We've gotten some very, very good
deals through them. The kids love to get the catalog in the mail and "window
shop" through it for weeks. After they've had time to evaluate, we usually
order a couple of things. Their tempera paint is pretty good ( not superb,
but fine for run of the mill painting) and very inexpensive.

**** Kim ****
runs with scissors

messages.subject: Re: Craft Resources?
messages.msgSnippet: Hi Ann: I don t know how cheap they are in comparison to any other online sources, but we have purchased a few things from the following site:
messages.messageBody:
Hi Ann:

I don't know how cheap they are in comparison to any other online sources,
but we have purchased a few things from the following site:

http://www.earlychildhood.com/

It's called "Discount School Supply." I first got their catalog from a
friend, then saw the site online. It's mainly aimed at teachers, so a lot
of items come in bulk. I hope this helps. See what you think.

Olivia

messages.messageBody:
I'm wondering if anyone has a source for inexpensive craft supplies

drive, and being in one is a nightmare with 3 small kids.
Ideas?
